Project No: 0004
Project Name: Getting Current Date and Time in Django
ðŸ“Œ Concept:

In Django, we can use Pythonâ€™s built-in datetime module to fetch the current date and time.
Example:
import datetime
dt = datetime.datetime.now()
print(dt)              # 2025-05-06 18:03:07.603018
print(dt.year)         # 2025
print(dt.month)        # 5
print(dt.day)          # 6
print(dt.hour)         # 18
print(dt.minute)       # 3
print(dt.second)       # 7
print(dt.microsecond)  # 603018

print(dt.strftime('%a'))  # Tue   (short day name)
print(dt.strftime('%A'))  # Tuesday (full day name)
print(dt.strftime('%W'))  # Week number
print(dt.strftime('%w'))  # Day number of week (0=Sunday)
print(dt.strftime('%m'))  # Month number

ðŸ“Œ Step 1: Project Creation
django-admin startproject DateTimeProject

ðŸ“Œ Step 2: Enter into the Project
cd DateTimeProject

ðŸ“Œ Step 3: Create the Application
py manage.py startapp DateTimeApp

ðŸ“Œ Step 4: Install the Application in Settings

DateTimeProject/settings.py

INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'DateTimeApp',
]

ðŸ“Œ Step 5: Define the View Function
DateTimeApp/views.py

from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse
import datetime

def date_time_view(request):
    # Get current date and time
    dt = datetime.datetime.now()

    # Format date and time
    today_date = dt.strftime("%d/%m/%Y")   # e.g., 22/08/2025
    current_time = dt.strftime("%H:%M:%S") # e.g., 10:57:34

    # HTML response with simple clean design
    data = f"""
    <html>
        <head>
            <title>Date and Time Application</title>
            <style>
                body {{
                    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
                    background-color: #f8f9fa;
                    color: #333;
                    padding: 20px;
                }}
                .container {{
                    max-width: 500px;
                    margin: auto;
                    background: #fff;
                    padding: 20px;
                    border-radius: 10px;
                    box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
                    text-align: center;
                }}
                h1 {{
                    color: #0066cc;
                    margin-bottom: 20px;
                }}
                p {{
                    font-size: 18px;
                    margin: 10px 0;
                }}
            </style>
        </head>
        <body>
            <div class="container">
                <h1>Current Date and Time</h1>
                <p><b>Today Date:</b> {today_date}</p>
                <p><b>Time:</b> {current_time}</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </html>
    """
    return HttpResponse(data)

ðŸ“Œ Step 6: Configure URL Pattern
DateTimeProject/urls.py

from django.contrib import admin
from django.urls import path
from DateTimeApp import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('admin/', admin.site.urls),
    path('get_date_time/', views.date_time_view),
]

ðŸ“Œ Step 7: Run the Server and Test
